    Now, what if you drop _another_ mushroom? Would it just grow bigger and bigger forever with every new mushroom? I liked that idea, but also didn‚Äôt want the site to ever look too wonky. I decided to account for each drop zone accepting two mushrooms and two potions max.

    So knowing we‚Äôll only have two mushrooms ever in the header, we can use `:has()` with the general sibling combinator to do that:


    ```css
    .header:has(.mushroom ~ .mushroom:not(.gu-transit)) {
      --header-height: 600px;
    }
    ```

    This makes the SVG `600px` tall when the header has two mushrooms that are siblings (again, not in transit).

